<br>
From experience.  If you want to camp rage you have to do a few things.  First of all -- get as much sleep as you can the first two days.  The third and possibly fourth day of the spawn is when you have to be relentless.  If you don't really want to sit AFK for 80 hours, then get a druid or a ranger to periodically log on and track rage every couple hours while you get some hunting done in a nearby zone.<br>
<br>
Be ready for people that will try to steal the spawn because it will happen.  And don't be dissapointed if it gets KS'd from you because alot of people don't care that a cleric invested all his/her time camping rage -- they just want their epic kthxbye. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Its a crappy camp.  I personally refuse to do it again.  Good luck getting him, and feel free to send me a tell if you need help killing him.<br>
<br>
